Fix error at compiling src/slave.c on cygwin
--------------------------------------------
Cygwin gcc includes src/rt/signal.h at #include <signal.h> in sys/poll.h.
This is really odd.
Maybe, real fix is fix cygwin gcc itself.
One of workaround is rename src/rt/signal.h.

On rename-signal-h branch, I renamed signal.h to usignal.h.
To do so, I can get nvc.exe but it's a bit awkward to me.

See more details:

 $ uname -a
 CYGWIN_NT-5.1 jabberwocky 1.7.10(0.259/5/3) 2012-02-05 12:36 i686 Cygwin

 $ ls /usr/include/signal.h
 /usr/include/signal.h

 $ grep -e '#include' /usr/include/poll.h
 #include <sys/poll.h>

 $ grep -e '#include' /usr/include/sys/poll.h
 #include <sys/cdefs.h>
 #include <sys/types.h>
 #include <signal.h>

